<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                    <head>No. 41.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Phelps</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-07-27"><hi rend="italic">July</hi> 27,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have read with pleasure your No. 6, of the
                        2d instant, relative to the restrictions upon the importation of American
                        pork into Austria-Hungary. Your representations thereon appear to have been
                        energetic and discreet, and are approved, as reflecting the views of this
                        Department.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>